President Obama issued a statement congratulating Ed Markey on his election to the United States Senate in Massachusetts. The President praised Markey's leadership on various issues, including carbon pollution, gun violence, and job creation. He commended Markey's reputation as an effective and bipartisan legislator. The President also thanked Mo Cowan for his work and John Kerry for his service in the Senate, as Kerry agreed to become Secretary of State. The President expressed confidence that Markey will continue Kerry's legacy and work with him on strengthening the economy, protecting the middle class, and expanding opportunity.